HEADWORD: Rebellious
<hw>Re*bel"lious</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*b⟦ecr⟧l"y⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Engaged in rebellion; disposed to rebel; of the nature of rebels or
of rebellion; resisting government or lawful authority by force.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Thy <xex>rebellious</xex> crew.⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧Proud
<xex>rebellious</xex> arms.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Re*bel"lious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*bel"lious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

